# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Supabase — pull from Vercel (do NOT hardcode). The Supabase vars live in the
# Vercel *Production* env, so the default `vercel env pull` (development) returns
# only VERCEL_OIDC_TOKEN. Use:
#   vercel env pull .env.local --environment=production --scope billys-projects-7712fade
#
# NOTE: the legacy `anon`/`service_role` JWT keys were DISABLED 2026-06-03 — this
# project is on Supabase's new key system. Use the publishable key as the anon key
# and the secret key as the service-role key (the old JWTs now 401 "Legacy API
# keys are disabled").
#
# GOTCHA: NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL / NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY / NEXT_PUBLIC_SITE_URL
# are flagged "Sensitive" in Vercel, so `env pull` returns them BLANK. Backfill them
# locally from their non-sensitive twins: URL from SUPABASE_URL, anon from
# SUPABASE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY, and set the site URL below for local dev.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project.supabase.co
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=sb_publishable_...        # publishable key (new system)
SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=sb_secret_...                 # secret key (new system; server-only, admin paths)

# Site URL (for OAuth redirect)
NEXT_PUBLIC_SITE_URL=http://localhost:3000

# Feedback → GitHub workflow
# Token with issues:write (push) access on the repo below. Used server-side
# only when an admin approves feedback.
GITHUB_TOKEN=your-github-token-here
# owner/repo that approved feedback opens issues in (defaults to billye2/xpbbs)
GITHUB_REPO=billye2/xpbbs
# Admin access is NOT configured here. Who may review feedback / see admin UI is
# the `app_admins` allowlist table in Supabase (see docs/environment.md). No
# email — personal or placeholder — is requested in config.

# Remote DB migrations: no env-stored DB credentials needed here. Apply them either
# via the Supabase MCP (apply_migration, authorize once per machine) OR the Supabase
# CLI — `supabase link --project-ref aennreackkegaqwwbowg` then `supabase db push`
# (needs a Personal Access Token: SUPABASE_ACCESS_TOKEN, from the dashboard).
# Project ref is aennreackkegaqwwbowg (purrfect-bbs, us-east-1).

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Proactive engine (Phase 4) — the digest emails stay DORMANT until these are set.
# Code ships safe-without-secrets: no key ⇒ the cron sends nothing.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Bearer secret the cron route checks (constant-time). Also set it in the cron
# trigger (Vercel Cron sets it automatically; pg_cron must send the header).
CRON_SECRET=
# Resend (email). Verify cubemetrics.com in Resend + add SPF/DKIM DNS on NameSilo.
RESEND_API_KEY=
NOTIFY_FROM=XP Boost <hello@cubemetrics.com>
# HMAC secret for one-click unsubscribe tokens.
NOTIFY_SIGNING_SECRET=
# To activate scheduling: add a cron hitting /api/cron/digest every ~30 min
# (Vercel Pro `*/30 * * * *`, or Supabase pg_cron). Keep the select.ts window
# >= the cron interval so no send window is missed.

# AI insight line (Phase 5). The Today insight ships deterministic (no AI) today.
# To upgrade to AI-written lines: `npm i ai zod`, set both below, and wire the
# model at src/lib/ai/nudge-input.ts::getNudge (see docs/app-plans/spine-phase5.md).
AI_NUDGES_ENABLED=
AI_GATEWAY_API_KEY=
